run the following code in v1.01 failed, while v0.708.1.0 works fine.

{code}
use MongoDB;
use boolean;
use Scalar::Util qw(refaddr);
use v5.20;
my $client = MongoDB::MongoClient->new;
my $db = $client->get_database( 'test' );
 my $collection= $db->get_collection( 'test' );

$collection->insert({"okay" => false, "name" => "fred0"});
$collection->insert({"okay" => false, "name" => "fred1"});
$collection->insert({"okay" => false, "name" => "fred2"});

my @docs = $collection->find()->all;
say(refaddr($_->{okay})) for @docs;
$_->{okay} = $_->{okay}->TO_JSON for @docs;

use DDP; p $_ for @docs;
{code}

Perl Version 5.1.8 on Max OS X 10.10.5
Using MongoDB v1.0.1 Perl module

Attempting to MongoDB:Collection->aggregate and continue to receive following error message: "Can't call method "next" on unblessed reference" using the following code:
{code}
my @pipeline = (
 	{ '$match' => { active => 1, name => 'jawbone_up'}},
	{ '$group' => { _id => user_id, count => { '$sum' => 1}}},
	{ '$sort' => { count => -1}},
	{ '$match' => { count => { '$gt' => 1}}},
	{ '$limit' => 25}
	);

my $cursor = $collection->aggregate( \@pipeline );

my $result = $cursor->next;
{code}

With the exception of the actual "matching/grouping" fields/values this matches the example shown in the meta::cpan documentation.

This is a common pattern than could us a helper:
{noformat}
$doc = $coll->find_one( { _id => $id } );
{noformat}

We could make that much easier like this:
{noformat}
$doc = $coll->find_id( $id );
{noformat}

Or treat the first element to find_one as an id if it's not a document.
{noformat}
$doc = $coll->find_one( $id );
{noformat}

my $client = MongoDB->connect('mongodb://@localhost');
my $coll = $client->ns('mydb.mycoll');
my $res = $coll->update(…);
if($res->acknowledged) {…}
> Can't call method "acknowledged" on unblessed reference

